    <para id="imp-id1171669115468">The average deviation from the mean is 6.8 ± 4.6. This is telling us about the precision of our data.
    </para><para id="imp-id1171669783150">The average deviation of the mean is 6.8 ± 4.6/√5. This is telling us about the accuracy of our data. 
    </para><para id="imp-id1171667804775">More information on the effectiveness of Mean Absolute Deviation over standard deviation can be found in Stephen Gorard paper Revisiting a 90-year-old debate: the advantages of the mean deviation. It can be found at 
<link url="http://www.leeds.ac.uk/educol/documents/00003759.htm">http://www.leeds.ac.uk/educol/documents/00003759.htm</link>
    </para></content>
  
